.TH "sys_tkill" 9 "sys_tkill" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_tkill \- send signal to one specific task
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_tkill
.BI "(pid_t pid "  ","
.BI "int sig "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pid" 12
the PID of the task
.IP "sig" 12
signal to be sent

Send a signal to only one task, even if it's a CLONE_THREAD task.
